# .dockerignore
#
# This file tells Docker which files to EXCLUDE from the build context.
# The build context is the folder you pass to docker build.
# Everything in that folder gets sent to the Docker daemon before building.
#
# WHY THIS MATTERS
#
# Without .dockerignore:
#   docker build sends your entire project folder to the daemon
#   including target/, .idea/, .git/ and node_modules/
#   This can be hundreds of megabytes sent on every build
#   It also risks accidentally copying secrets into your image
#
# With .dockerignore:
#   Only the files Docker actually needs are sent
#   Builds are faster because less data is transferred
#   Images are safer because junk files cannot accidentally get in

# ── Java and Maven build output ───────────────────────────────────────
# The target folder contains compiled classes and built JARs
# These are generated by Maven and should never be copied into an image
# Docker should always compile fresh inside the container
target/

# Compiled class files left over from manual javac runs
*.class

# ── IntelliJ IDEA project files ───────────────────────────────────────
# These are IDE configuration files specific to your machine
# They have no place inside a Docker image
.idea/
*.iml
*.iws
*.ipr
out/

# ── Git history ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Your entire git history should never be inside a Docker image
# It adds size and exposes your commit history
.git/
.gitignore
.gitattributes

# ── OS generated files ───────────────────────────────────────────────
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini

# ── Logs ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
*.log
logs/

# ── Secrets — never let these reach an image ─────────────────────────
.env
*.env.*
*.key
*.pem
secrets/

# ── Documentation ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# README files are useful on GitHub but not inside a running container
README.md
docs/

# ── Test files ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Test code should never run in a production image
# It also adds unnecessary size
src/test/